# phase-claude-md-modularize.log — v1.97.6

Goal: split CLAUDE.md so portable conventions live in their own doc that
another project can copy, and the active per-PR ledger lives in its own
doc. CLAUDE.md becomes a slim index pointing at both, plus the
project-specific rules that don't fit either.

## M1 — audit + borderline surfacing

Audited CLAUDE.md (pre-PR: 146 lines, ~134 KB — the entire 51-entry
recent ledger lived inline) and all 17 files under `docs/`. Catalogued
every rule + section into three buckets:

- **Portable** (any project on any stack could copy verbatim): stale-
  worktree protocol, plan-then-ship autonomy, auto-merge policy + report-
  back rule, version-bump rule, per-push reporting 3-point template, test
  rule, end-to-end verification + stash-pop, maintenance rule, Bash
  discipline, working-with-subagents (all 7 points), rollback Layer 1
  pattern.
- **Project-specific** (stays in CLAUDE.md or topical doc): t9l intro
  paragraph + version pin, autonomy permissions list, admin-orthogonal-
  UX, no-exports-from-'use server', cache-invalidation canonical, all
  topical docs (architecture / auth / data-model / time-handling /
  domain-migration / known-infra-issues / etc.).
- **Borderline** (need operator call): migration SQL discipline, post-
  deploy verification, rollback layer model, admin-orthogonal-UX (the
  principle has portable shape but the signals are t9l-specific),
  'use server' exports rule (Next.js-specific), cache invalidation (Next.
  js-specific).

Surfaced the borderline list to the operator with proposed splits for
each. Operator confirmed all six: B1 (migration SQL) + B2 (post-deploy
verification) + B3 (rollback layers) get portable principles in
methodology.md WITH pointers to the project-specific implementation;
B4–B6 stay entirely in their topical docs (admin-orthogonal-UX,
'use server' exports, cache invalidation) because they're either
Next.js-specific or use t9l-specific signals.

## M2 — docs/methodology.md written

New 200-line doc covering the portable conventions in 11 sections:
Stale-worktree protocol / Plan-then-ship autonomy / Auto-merge policy /
Version-bump rule / Per-push reporting / Test rule / End-to-end
verification / Maintenance rule / ORM migration discipline / Post-deploy
verification / Rollback layer model / Working with subagents / Bash
discipline / Adopting this file in a new project.

Style: prose mode, generic placeholders (`<parent-repo-path>` instead of
`/Users/stefan/t9l-website`), references to "the project's
release-and-ship.md" / "the ORM's create-only command" rather than
named-stack specifics. The doc is meant to be copy-pasted into another
project's `docs/methodology.md` with only the bottom "Adopting" section
needing edits.

Stack-agnostic regression target: a test asserts the file contains no
literal `T9L`, `Tennozu`, or `t9l.me` strings — accidental leakage of
project-specific terminology back into the portable doc would fail.

## M3 — docs/ledger.md written

Lifted the 52 active ledger paragraphs (v1.97.5 → v1.79.1) from CLAUDE.md
into a new docs/ledger.md with a 13-line preamble + the entries +
archive-pointer footer. Path rewrites for in-text markdown links:

- `docs/release-and-ship.md` → `release-and-ship.md` (sister doc).
- `docs/perf-phase3-lcp-handoff.md` → `perf-phase3-lcp-handoff.md`.
- `handover-edit-details-audit.md` → `../handover-edit-details-audit.md`
  (repo-root reference from docs/).
- All 11 `phase-X.log` references → `../phase-X.log`.

Verified zero broken relative links by listing each `](path)` occurrence
and resolving from the docs/ledger.md location. The 113 KB ledger body
was assembled via shell composition (`cat header + entries + footer`)
rather than a single Write call to avoid blowing up the conversation
token budget.

## M4 — CLAUDE.md slimmed

Rewrote CLAUDE.md from scratch as a 67-line index. Sections:

1. Project intro paragraph (T9L.me, stack, multi-tenant slug routing).
2. Current release + active ledger pointer + archive pointer.
3. How conventions are organised (methodology.md vs CLAUDE.md vs topical
   docs).
4. Topical docs table (extended with rows for `docs/methodology.md` and
   `docs/ledger.md`).
5. Stale-worktree protocol — short, points at methodology.md for the
   procedure, names this repo's specific paths (`/Users/stefan/t9l-website`).
6. Project-specific standing rules: autonomy permissions list, plan-
   then-ship stop conditions specific to t9l, auto-merge policy (kept
   inline because the gh command + release-and-ship.md anchor are repo-
   specific), version-bump target, admin-orthogonal-UX rule, no-exports
   rule, cache-invalidation canonical, migration SQL Prisma-specific
   pointer, post-deploy verification target, maintenance rule.

Pre-PR line count: 146. Post-PR line count: 70. ~52 % reduction in
lines and ~95 % reduction in bytes (since ledger entries were enormous).

## M5 — verification + test migration + ship

### M5a — test impact

Found 21 test files referencing CLAUDE.md; of those only 7 actually call
`readFileSync` against the file, and of those only 3 assert content that
moved or was eliminated:

- `v1.95.1` and `v1.95.2`: both assert a `**Auto-merge policy.**` block
  exists in CLAUDE.md with various markers. Resolved by keeping a
  one-paragraph auto-merge summary inline in CLAUDE.md's standing rules
  — that paragraph is genuinely project-specific (it names the exact
  `gh pr merge --squash --admin` command and the `docs/release-and-ship
  .md#auto-merge-policy` anchor). The generic principle still lives in
  methodology.md; the inline paragraph references it.
- `v1.97.1`: asserts `## Recent ledger` section + top bullet in CLAUDE.
  md. Migrated to read `docs/ledger.md` instead — the "top bullet is
  newest" pin is still meaningful in the new home.

The remaining 4 file-reading tests (`v187` retire-player, `v188` guest
refactor, `v192` availability list-view, `v196` payment-banner toggle)
only assert the `**Current release:**` header pattern, which is
unchanged.

### M5b — new regression-target test

New `tests/unit/v1976_doc_modularisation.test.ts` pins the split:

- APP_VERSION ≥ 1.97.6 + CLAUDE.md header matches.
- `docs/methodology.md` exists with all 10 portable-rule section
  headers (stale-worktree, plan-then-ship, auto-merge, version-bump,
  per-push, ORM migration, post-deploy, rollback, subagents, Bash).
- Methodology stack-agnostic: NO occurrence of `T9L` / `Tennozu` /
  `t9l.me` in the doc.
- `docs/ledger.md` exists, top bullet is recent (v1.9x.x pattern),
  contains ≥10 bullets, references ledger-archive.md.
- CLAUDE.md is ≤ 100 lines (slim-index discipline guard).
- CLAUDE.md points at methodology.md AND ledger.md.
- CLAUDE.md NO LONGER carries `## Recent ledger` section (regression
  target — if a future PR drops ledger paragraphs back inline it fails).
- Project-specific rules retained in CLAUDE.md: admin-orthogonal-UX
  pointer, 'use server' rule, revalidate canonical, prisma migrate
  create-only, post-deploy verification pointer.

### M5c — local verification + ship

Run vitest + tsc, push PR, self-merge per the v1.95.1 + v1.95.2 auto-
merge policy. Tests should all pass; tsc should be clean (no source
code changes outside `src/lib/version.ts`). Per-push report + post-
deploy report follow the standard 3-point template.
